e Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Lovett was born about 1128, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richardus De Louet, was 39 and his mother, Mrs Richard De Louet, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Isabel Saint Maur."},"et":{"ABT 1128–":"umbes 1128–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1131–Female":"1131–Surnud","1154–Male":"1154–Surnud","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Surnud","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1128":"1128","1115":"1115","1154":"1154","1131":"1131","ABT 1128":"umbes 1128","1150":"1150",", NORTHAMPTONSHIRE, EN":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1128–":"noin 1128–Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1128–Male":"1128–Kuollut","1131–Female":"1131–Kuollut","1154–Male":"1154–Kuollut","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Kuollut","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1128":"1128","1115":"1115","1154":"1154","1131":"1131","ABT 1128":"noin 1128","1150":"1150",", NORTHAMPTONSHIRE, EN":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1128–":"environ 1128–Décédé","1115–Male":"1115–Décédé","1128–Male":"1128–Décédé","1131–Female":"1131–Décédée","1154–Male":"1154–Décédé","1090–1150":"1090–1150","1106–Female":"110